#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.50"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.50:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.50:0.2"
msgid "5. Cūḷavagga"
msgstr "5. The Lesser Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.50:0.3"
msgid "50. Mahācorasutta"
msgstr "50. A Master Thief"

# Note: BB has “commits banditry” for ekagarika, but cf. MW: aikāgārika as, ī mf. (fr. ekâgāra • ekam asahāyam āgāram prayojanam asya, whose object is a solitary house), a thief Pāṇ. 5-1, 113 Daś. Śiś.; which agrees with pali comms “ekam eva gharaṁ parivāretvā vilumpanaṁ”, see CPD.
#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.50:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato mahācoro sandhimpi chindati, nillopampi "
"harati, ekāgārikampi karoti, paripanthepi tiṭṭhati."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a master thief with three factors breaks into houses, plunders "
"wealth, steals from isolated buildings, and commits highway robbery."

msgctxt "an3.50:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi tīhi?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.50:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, mahācoro visamanissito ca hoti, gahananissito ca hoti, "
"balavanissito ca hoti."
msgstr ""
"A master thief relies on uneven ground, on thick cover, and on powerful "
"individuals."

msgctxt "an3.50:1.4"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, mahācoro visamanissito hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a master thief rely on uneven ground?"

msgctxt "an3.50:1.5"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, mahācoro nadīviduggaṃ vā nissito hoti pabbatavisamaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a master thief relies on inaccessible riverlands or rugged "
"mountains."

msgctxt "an3.50:1.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, mahācoro visamanissito hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a master thief relies on uneven ground."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.154"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.50:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, mahācoro gahananissito hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a master thief rely on thick cover?"

# Note: BB reads “gedha”, citing PTS, and translates “coppice”, but PTS only has gedha in this (dubious) case, and it says “cave” (=geha?). I can’t find anything to justify “coppice”. On the other hand, India is full of raised banks and ridges in paddies, perfect to hide behind, so “rodha” it is.
#. VAR: rodhaṃ → gedhaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.50:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, mahācoro tiṇagahanaṃ vā nissito hoti, rukkhagahanaṃ vā "
"rodhaṃ vā mahāvanasaṇḍaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a master thief relies on thick grass, thick trees, a ridge, or a "
"large dense wood."

msgctxt "an3.50:2.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, mahācoro gahananissito hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a master thief relies on thick cover."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.50:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, mahācoro balavanissito hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a master thief rely on powerful individuals?"

msgctxt "an3.50:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, mahācoro rājānaṃ vā rājamahāmattānaṃ vā nissito hoti."
msgstr "It’s when a master thief relies on rulers or their ministers."

msgctxt "an3.50:3.3"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "an3.50:3.4"
msgid ""
"‘sace maṃ koci kiñci vakkhati, ime me rājāno vā rājamahāmattā vā pariyodhāya "
"atthaṃ bhaṇissantī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If anyone accuses me of anything, these rulers or their ministers will "
"speak in my defense in the case.’"

msgctxt "an3.50:3.5"
msgid ""
"Sace naṃ koci kiñci āha, tyāssa rājāno vā rājamahāmattā vā pariyodhāya "
"atthaṃ bhaṇanti."
msgstr "And that’s exactly what happens."

msgctxt "an3.50:3.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, mahācoro balavanissito hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a master thief relies on powerful individuals."

msgctxt "an3.50:3.7"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhave, tīhi aṅgehi samannāgato mahācoro sandhimpi chindati, "
"nillopampi harati, ekāgārikampi karoti, paripanthepi tiṭṭhati."
msgstr ""
"A master thief with these three factors breaks into houses, plunders wealth, "
"steals from isolated buildings, and commits highway robbery."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.50:4.1"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tīhi aṅgehi samannāgato pāpabhikkhu khataṃ upahataṃ "
"attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ "
"pasavati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when a bad mendicant has three factors, they keep "
"themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by "
"sensible people, and they make much bad karma."

msgctxt "an3.50:4.2"
msgid "Katamehi tīhi?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.50:4.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu visamanissito ca hoti gahananissito ca "
"balavanissito ca."
msgstr ""
"A bad mendicant relies on uneven ground, on thick cover, and on powerful "
"individuals."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.50:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu visamanissito hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a bad mendicant rely on uneven ground?"

msgctxt "an3.50:5.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu visamena kāyakammena samannāgato hoti, visamena "
"vacīkammena samannāgato hoti, visamena manokammena samannāgato hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a bad mendicant has unethical conduct by way of body, speech, and "
"mind."

msgctxt "an3.50:5.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu visamanissito hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a bad mendicant relies on uneven ground."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an3.50:6.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu gahananissito hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a bad mendicant rely on thick cover?"

msgctxt "an3.50:6.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu micchādiṭṭhiko hoti, antaggāhikāya diṭṭhiyā "
"samannāgato hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a bad mendicant has wrong view, he’s attached to an extremist view."

msgctxt "an3.50:6.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu gahananissito hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a bad mendicant relies on thick cover."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.155"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an3.50:7.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu balavanissito hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a bad mendicant rely on powerful individuals?"

msgctxt "an3.50:7.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu rājānaṃ vā rājamahāmattānaṃ vā nissito hoti."
msgstr "It’s when a bad mendicant relies on rulers or their ministers."

msgctxt "an3.50:7.3"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "an3.50:7.4"
msgid ""
"‘sace maṃ koci kiñci vakkhati, ime me rājāno vā rājamahāmattā vā pariyodhāya "
"atthaṃ bhaṇissantī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If anyone accuses me of anything, these rulers or their ministers will "
"speak in my defense in the case.’"

msgctxt "an3.50:7.5"
msgid ""
"Sace naṃ koci kiñci āha, tyāssa rājāno vā rājamahāmattā vā pariyodhāya "
"atthaṃ bhaṇanti."
msgstr "And that’s exactly what happens."

msgctxt "an3.50:7.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu balavanissito hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a bad mendicant relies on powerful individuals."

msgctxt "an3.50:7.7"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhi dhammehi samannāgato pāpabhikkhu khataṃ upahataṃ "
"attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ "
"pasavatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"When a bad mendicant has these three factors, they keep themselves broken "
"and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, "
"and they make much bad karma.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.50:7.8"
msgid "Ekādasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.50:7.9"
msgid "Cūḷavaggo pañcamo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an3.50:8.1"
msgid "Sammukhī ṭhānatthavasaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.50:8.2"
msgid "pavatti paṇḍita sīlavaṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.50:8.3"
msgid "Saṅkhataṃ pabbatātappaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
#. VAR: mahācorenekādasāti → mahācorenekārasāti (s1-3) | mahācorena te dasāti (mr)
msgctxt "an3.50:8.4"
msgid "mahācorenekādasāti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "an3.50:8.5"
msgid "Paṭhamo paṇṇāsako samatto."
msgstr ""
